issue.title: Update `AMP_Core_Block_Handler` to handle interactivity API enabled blocks
issue.body:
### Bug Description

With https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/pull/54297 the support for disabling interactivity API has been removed due to which the `core/navigation` block now is using interactivity API by default.

issue.title: Canonical url not generate properly
issue.body:
### Bug Description

Dear team, 

had install this plugin and checked that canonical tag was not generated properly 

for i.e. this is my amp page 
https://goklassifieds.com/listing/siliguri-college/amp/

and its canonical url must be
https://goklassifieds.com/listing/siliguri-college/

but plugin is generating 
https://goklassifieds.com/?post_type=listing&p=11507

canonical url must be generate below link

issue.title: Omit page caching and object caching tests for Site Health if on WP>=6.1
issue.body:
### Feature Description

New description from @westonruter:  The Site Health tests for page caching and object caching from the AMP plugin have been incorporated into WordPress core as of 6.1. See https://github.com/WordPress/performance/issues/220 ([Core-56041](https://core.trac.wordpress.org/ticket/56041)) and https://github.com/WordPress/performance/issues/35 ([Core-56040](https://core.trac.wordpress.org/ticket/56040)). At the very least these tests can be disabled in WP  6.1+. But I think it would be better to just remove them entirely.

<details><summary>Original description</summary>

We got a [support topic](https://wordpress.org/support/topic/amp-cache-error/) where the user is getting a site health a warning for cache plugin, although he is using a cache plugin (Litespeed cache) because LiteSpeed uses a different header it's not able to detect it.

The Litespeed author suggested that we use a filter so that other vendors can pass their headers so it will fix warnings for their plugins.

</details>
